1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object detection and performance estimation in images/videos. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses statistical methods to estimate detector performance. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with the problem of generalization in object detection. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions false detections and precision, which are relevant to security applications. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also less likely but possible as the paper uses pooled testing approaches, which have been used in information retrieval tasks such as document clustering.
